n und dem statistischen Zugang zur Thermodynamik. Es ist aus experimenteller Perspektive geschrieben und vermeidet einige Grundlagenprobleme der traditionellen Darstellungsweise. Die allgemeinen Konzepte werden durch zahlreiche Anwendungen von Alltagsphänomenen über die Festkörperphysik bis hin zur Physik der Nanostrukturen illustriert.  aThis book provides an innovative bridge between traditional and statistical approaches to thermodynamics. It is written from an experimental perspective and avoids the basic difficulties and inconsistencies of traditional presentations. The author elucidates the basic concepts of macroscopic thermodynamics using familiar systems of mechanics and electricity before addressing the particular features of thermal energy phenomena.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Jun 2020) 0aStatistische Thermodynamik. 4aBOOK. 4aMakro. 4aMikrowelt. 4aModerne. 4aStrunk. 4aThermodynamik. 4aZwischen. 7aSCIENCE / Mechanics / Thermodynamics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics, Physics 2014z9783110370355oZDB-23-DEM0 cEPUBz978311039679940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110371062423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110371062.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEMb2014  aZDB-23-DGGb2014